description: Does Archie have a chance when he submits photos to the local newspaper's Winter Wonderland competition, or will he be 'Freeze Framed' with a frosty reception? Plus, puzzles, games, pin-ups, and more!

It's a 'Happy Birthday... Not!' when Archie, tired of being pulled at like a stick of taffy, decides to spend his birthday apart from Betty and Veronica - but for how long? Then, Archie discovers he has seasonal allergies - namely winter snow shoveling and spring cleaning - when get gets a 'Cold Shoulder!' And there's 'Trouble in Store' when Mr. Andrews decides to take up a new sport - competitive grocery shopping!
Archie needs a 'Catch Phrase' as tries to be the 'early bird' at the fishing hole, but while the fish are biting, it's sleep Archie's fighting!

Feeling the stress of studies, extracurricular activities and college applications, the gang decides to put the Archies on hiatus - until Jughead convinces his bandmates to appear in a high school musical he's written about a teen rock band stressed out by their studies, extracurricular activities and college applications! Then, a short time ago, in a town called Riverdale not too far away, Jughead has dragged Archie to a toy store at midnight so he can be among the first to purchase the new Star Lores action figures! Finally, Archie's convinced that petting Betty's cat Carmel is good luck before an exam - but the only thing between Archie and a passing grade is the tree Carmel's stuck in!

It's no mere 'Voting Game' when Archie and Reggie run against one another for class president. Then, Archie learns how fleeting is the 'Fame Game' when he fumbles a football. Also, Little Archie and his friends are back in 'The Riverdale Elementary School Musical' when Little Archie and his friends prove that high schoolers aren't the only ones who can put on musicals in this tuneful tale!

Mr. Lodge decides to enter the classic car he bought from Archie's grandfather in in an antique auto competition - but the car is stolen before the contest begins! Who did it, and what was their 'motor-vation'? Then, Archie dreams of winning gold in the cold by becoming an Olympic snowboarder, but wait until he sees how many hills he has to climb to get there - literally! Finally, Archie and his dad decide to let Mrs. Andrews sleep in after a busy week - now if only they can keep quiet! Plus, puzzles, games, pin-ups, and more!

'Big, Big Sleep': Feeling sleep-deprived, Archie turns to the one person who's a model of rest and relaxation - Jughead! Will Archie ever wake up now? 'The Past was a Blast': An 80th birthday party for Archie's grandfather makes the kids reconsider their attitude that older folks 'missed out' on all their modern-day fun. 'On the Spot': Feeling self-conscious over the freckles on his ears, Archie takes to wearing earmuffs... all the time!
name: The Big Big Sleep

description: For Archie, modern homework is more about text messaging than text books! Then, Little Archie visits his grandparents' farm and meets all their new animals, including a monkey that's just like him! Finally, while waiting for Veronica to get off the phone, Jughead and Archie eat all the appetizers prepared for Mrs. Lodge's fundraiser! Time for the merry munchers to make fast with alternate hors d'oeuvres!

Archie has a 'big fish' story to tell, all about the big mess he made at the new seafood restaurant! Then, waiters on wheels are back in style, but when Archie is your server you might want to take insurance on your meal! Finally, a tree by any other name would still rain chestnuts down all over town!

Francine returns from Tennessee determined to find a man and begin a new life. But when she goes back to the rent house to get her things, she finds that David and Katchoo have already left, and they¹re not coming back! Will she accept their invitation to join them in an idyllic life in Hawaii, or will she stick to her decision to become the suburban mom of her dreams? It¹s a tough day for the girls that is rudely interrupted when Francine discovers Freddie has the nude painting of her hanging in his living room!

Francine is in a wedding dress stood on the ledge of an apartment building and she is having second thoughts. He relatives are asking what she is doing and she says she is thinking. Someone grabs her ankle and she falls but held up by the ankle. Her face is now level with a lower window with Katchoo inside and below on the pavement is a duck in a tuxedo. Katchoo asks if she can save her but she falls before she can take her hand.

Francine wakes on the bedroom floor as Katchoo checks in on her. She's decided not to join them on the New York trip. When Katchoo fails to ask why they argue about Katchoo's lack of caring and Francine's lack of commitment and when asked what Kat's intentions are with David she tells her she's doing what Francine should be doing with her. Katchoo shouts that though she loves Francine she can't commit while David has risked his life and given her his love over and over and she can't ignore it anymore.

A Broken Francine is left alone when Casey calls. Freddie has left her and Francine goes to comfort her. Francine comforts the devastated Casey who tells her its impossible when you love someone who love someone else.

On the plane Katchoo needs a drink when the plane suddenly loses control pitching people and object all over the cabin. They regain control and apologies as they seem to have lost hydraulic tail control but are only 60miles from the airstrip. David gets up to help the injured and Katchoo phones Francine who is out. Katchoo knows the plane is not going to make it. David asks if she was baptized, she confirms she was as a baby. He tells her she has to confess to Christ again now to be saved. She refuses and lists things she loves ending with "All I'll miss is you Francine"

At Casey Francine is in the bathroom and glimpses Katchoo in the mirror, she turns to talk to her and finds no-one there. She is gripped by a terrible fear and starts screaming
name: Running Late

description:
David finds himself at odds with the Big Six who want him to join their ranks and fill his sister's role. But Tambi has made it known to David that joining the covert group will cost him his life. Who is Tambi working for now, and why has David suddenly become the key ingredient for America's impending fall from power? This is the answer Katchoo is determined to find out before it's too late!

A four year old girl sits in a field of burning wreckage. Her mother dying in the field. The narrator tells of her story and how this night will effect everything she does and lead her to an early grave in just 12 years.

Katchoo sits in the still burning cabin when Emma appears. She sees burnt bodies everywhere and eventually finds David still in his seat. Emma watches without a word as the fire gets worse. She carries him until the a huge explosion knocks them down. Farmers come and try to help. they find David apparently dead in Katchoo's lap.

Francine is crying hard and says somethings happened, the plane must have crashed. They put on the news and the top story is the plane crash and the burning wreckage is on screen. Francine has her ticket and cries why didn't she stop Katchoo going. Francine calls her mother and lets her know too.

Elsewhere Tambi is training when she gets a call, she turns on the TV and asks the caller: what have they done! The callers tells her everything is sorted now and that Darcy's company come solely to them. Tambi threatens them if anything has happened to Katchoo. When the phone goes down she swears vengeance.

At the hospital Marie arrives and finds Katchoo on a gurney, unable to talk, and comforts her.
name: Dark The Sun

description: A horrible commercial airplane crash has claimed the lives of 153 people. Katchoo and David were on that plane, traveling to New York to claim his billion-dollar inheritance. As a distraught Francine arrives on the scene, she finds Katchoo alive but badly injured and David... missing! Was it all an unfortunate accident? When Katchoo receives a bedside phone call from Tambi, the horrible truth becomes clear. BONUS! This issue features a special full-color paperdoll insert on coated cardstock. Cut out the Francine and Katchoo figures on the insert and dress them in a variety of outfits that will appear on the back cover of upcoming SiP issues!
name: A Field of Lions

description: Katchoo, Francine, and David's lives have been changed forever by a horrible plane crash that turns out to be a sabotage. Knowing they will never be safe until their enemies are dealt with, Katchoo goes underground in an all-out assault ? Darcy Parker style! As an added bonus, the back cover of this issue features a complete set of clothes for the SIP paperdolls published in SIP #28. From cool, vamp, to downright sexy, Francine and Katchoo never looked so hot!
name: My Other Life

description: Katchoo sets out in search of the woman who wants to destroy her and her loved ones. But finding her won't be easy in the underground world of organized crime, so it's a good thing she has someone beside her to help in her quest ? Tambi! Meanwhile, Francine shifts her attention to David, who lies helpless in a hospital bed. Nursing him in his hour of need, David finally begins to open up to Francine, and tells her the story of his violent past. BONUS: The back cover of this issue features a new set of clothes for the SiP paperdolls (published in SiP#28).
name: I’m Open

description: Francine spends months by David's side, helping him recuperate from his serious injuries. With Katchoo absent, David shares the secrets of his violent past and the friendship between him and Francine grows until they become close ? very close. Meanwhile, Katchoo spends months retraining herself with only one goal in mind: revenge, and the complete annihilation of the enemies that have destroyed her life. PLUS! More Paper Dolls! Collect all the sexy new clothes for the Francine and Katchoo paper dolls!
name: The Black Of Your Heart

description: It's the annual SiP Special Summer One-Shot! The SiP gang is featured in a super-hero parody entitled "Not With My Cape You Don't!" with Francine as The Wallflower, Katchoo as Razormouth and David as Captain Ahhh! Casey dreams that she and her SiP friends are heroes battling Freddie Femur, as the arch-villain, Fex Femur, for world peace when he attempts to seize semi-control of a very small town outside of a major metropolitan area. (Sorry, but as the slacker generation hits the villain ranks, this is about as ambitious as they seem to get!)
name: When Worlds Collide!

description: Welcome to the fast lane, dear boy, it's New York City, SiP style! David's search for the underground Katchoo leads him to the heart of the powerful and deadly "Big Six" operation in downtown Manhattan, where he attempts to take his inherited seat alongside the leaders. The trouble is, they don't want him... in fact, they'd rather he were dead! Can David stay alive long enough to find his beloved Katchoo? Or perhaps more importantly, will he remain true to his peaceful faith or revert to the ultra-violent ways of his youth in order to survive and protect the woman he loves? The shocking answer is in this issue!
name: Crossroads

description: The wicked make war and Veronica is as wicked as they come, my friends! Armageddon begins as Veronica's plan to destroy the underworld establishment and create a new "disorder" bears fruit. Sal Tucciani, head of The Big Six and organized crime, declares war on Veronica's clan and Katchoo's small but powerful group, while the two girls are engaged in a deadly game of cat and mouse... the first one to be found dies! Will David be able to do anything to stop the fire of hate that has upset the delicate balance between these dark and complex factions? The solution may be found in Tambi, the cold, calculating killer who is playing everybody against each other in a nerve-wracking game of control, and reveals the shocking reason why in this issue! Meanwhile, back home, Francine prepares for her wedding and agonizes over just how white her dress should be.
name: Pretty Maids All In A Row

description: In the aftermath of their showdown against the Big Six, Francine and Katchoo return to Tennessee in hopes of rebuilding their life together. But they find an angry reception when it becomes clear that Francine's fiance, Brad, must compete for her attention against rival Katchoo! Sparks fly and someone is about to walk out of Francine's life forever! Find out in this stunning conclusion to one of the most powerful stories yet in the world of Paradise!
name: Child of Rage

description: From riches to rags, David may not be so wealthy after all! Uncle Sam comes looking for Darcy Parker's estate because it seems all of her money was gained illegally! Will David have to give all 1.4 million dollars back to the government? And what about the 10 million he gave Francine, will she have to give that back, too? Egad, this could be awkward! Find out how the two nicest people in paradise handle the setback of their lives in this issue!
name: Shhh!

description: There's good news and bad news. The good news is: Francine finally meets her fiance's famous brother, Griffin Silver. The bad news: it's love at first sight! And Griffin is not to be trusted in matters of love, even when it concern's his own brother's fiance! Meanwhile, David gives Katchoo a bold ultimatum and leaves for Hawaii. What is his demand? Find out in this new issue of SiP!
name: What A Loser Freddie Femur

description: Is Francine engaged to the right brother? She's beginning to have serious doubts after having met her fiance's famous rock star brother, Griffin Silver. But Katchoo offers a surprising solution to the dilemma ?? let's all go to the Bahamas for the weekend and see what happens! Put on your seatbelts, it's going to be a bumpy ride when bikinis, tequila, and too much fun in the sun bring out the truth in this bizarre foursome.
name: Lily

description:
An anthology based issue detailing various occurrences in outer space.   
 
Note:  One of the has based one of the characters off of a classic pose of Marilyn Monroe.

The Helicopter Blitz;

The Pirate Who Hated Blood;

Hitler’s Headsman;

Banshee O’Brien,

Boy Enchanter,

in the Mystery of the Modern Monster
name: The Helicopter Blitz

description: Picks up from events that occured in Femforce 37. Features villians Lady Luger and Fritz Voltzman by Bill Black and Mark Heike. Cameo appearances by Bolt, Paragon, Rad and other AC heroes. Plus a golden age reprint from 1941′s Daredevil Battles Hitler by Bob Davis.

Meet Pikachu and all-star Pokémon. From the Pokémon movies--two complete Pikachu short stories in one manga!

Pikachu's Vacation

The Pokémon have the day off and meet two new friends at the park: Marill and Snubbull! But even on vacation, can Raichu and Pikachu get along?

Pikachu's Rescue Adventure

While the Pokémon enjoy a summer nap, Togepi rolls down a hole in the ground and into a fabulous green world--a tree as big as a mountain! It's up to Pikachu and friends to rescue Togepi! But what strange Pokémon will they meet on the way?

Have you ever heard the story of how Francine posed for her sculptor boyfriend in college, only to find that he produced a full- size nude statue of her that was unveiled in the center of the student courtyard on Arts & Crafts Day?! Find out what happens next in the most embarrassing moment of Francine's life - the day she was expelled from college.
name: Something About You

description: In a strange turn of events, all the SIP girls end up at Casey's house for the evening, and before you know it, it's a slumber party! Katchoo, Francine, Casey, Margie and yes, even Tambi, in a night filled with T-shirts, bunny slippers, and a scathing review of love and mankind as seen through the eyes of the SIP girls! Come on, admit it, you've always wondered what Tambi looks like in a nightie! Well, here's your chance to find out. It's a perfect evening until Freddie and Chuck crash the party and all heck breaks loose! Trust us, this is one party you don't want to miss!
name: When Dreamers Wake

description: Things heat up when Francine spends time with David and Katchoo in the "Tropic Of Desire." This is one issue you do not want to miss! Sun, private beaches, long cool drinks, and close quarters bring pent-up desires to the surface in this long-awaited issue that will make your pulse race!
name: If I Cry Before I Wake

description: Marooned! Not a word you want to use to describe your situation, but that's exactly what happens to two of the most beloved SiP friends! Not going to say who, but one certain female goes for an afternoon sail with another certain female, and the two end up marooned on a deserted tropical island. With nothing but their bathing suits and a healthy supply of homemade margaritas, the fearless castaways suddenly find themselves in an uncomfortably intimate situation -- and that's when the sand hits the fan! Find out who ends up with whom in the latest waterlogged issue!
name: Brave New World

description: A lingerie edition featuring Playboy model Alley Baggett and a variety of artists making her look sexy...not that that would be tough!

They're back! Young, beautiful, and bursting with vitality -- it's Francine and Katchoo back in all their glory before any gangster or madwomen or middle-age crisis took them away to drama-land. Trust that if you're a SiP fan, you're going to like what you see!
name: In My Life

description: The names bring a shiver to anybody who knows their story. But what was Molly like as a teenager in high school, before the sex and blood that launched her into notoriety? Find out more in this issue when Francine's brother Benjamin throws all reason out the window and begins dating the weird but sensuous Molly Lane, despite the advice of his friends and family. Madness was never so darned appealing. Don't miss this sexy look at psychosis entitled, "Borderline Lover."
name: Stardust

description: This saga chronicles the adventures of the warrior, Almuric, who, after being hurled through space, finds himself on a strange planet populated with beautiful women and dangerous beasties!
name: Almuric

description: It's the story of Adam and Eve from Genesis, now retold in space.
This Series continues in the Fantoman series before returning with the final, second issue.
name: In This Issue - A Triple Fantom of the Fair Feature

description: Features Cave Girl written by Gardner Fox,art by Bob Powell. "The Amazon Assasins" from Cave Girl #12, "Altar of the Axe" from Cave Girl #13 and "The Shadow God of Korchak" from Thun'Da #4! Plus Nyoka the Jungle Girl in "Jungle Jaundice" art by Henry Kieffer from Master Comics 111!

A Dawn anthology written and illustrated by Joseph Michael Linsner based upon his chosen work completed between fall 1988 and summer 1994. They are meant to reflect his growth as a person and artist as specifically applied to his stories.

Writer Jason Aaron (Scalped) and artist Ron Garney (AMAZING SPIDER-MAN) bring you a searing epilogue to the biggest X-Men event in a decade. In the aftermath of Messiah CompleX, Wolverine has just one thing on his mind: revenge. But who is the focus of his rage, and what dark secret does he share with them? And how far over the edge is Wolverine willing to go to get what he wants? Collecting WOLVERINE #62-65.
name: TPB

description: The Green Goblin returns - will Spider-Man survive the rematch? Peter Parker has a secret. Bitten by a radioactive spider, he gained the powers of a human arachnid - super-strength, adhesion to walls and incredible agility. Inspired by his uncle's tragic death, Peter became Spider-Man, New York City's hometown super hero. Only two people know his secret identity - one is his best friend, confidante and girlfriend Mary Jane Watson. The other - ruthless businessman Norman Osborn, otherwise known as the Green Goblin. In their first battle, Norman nearly killed Peter before his own apparent death. But now, the Goblin has returned, more powerful than ever before. And Osborn will use his knowledge of Peter's double identity to control the teenager - threatening the lives of Mary Jane and his beloved Aunt May if Peter refuses to obey. Will Spider-Man be forced to serve his greatest enemy to protect his loved ones from harm? Collecting ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN #14-27.
name: Volume Two

concept_credits.name: With Great Power Comes Great Responsibility

first_appearance_concepts.name: With Great Power Comes Great Responsibility

description:
Indicia - Vol. 1, No. 1, 1946.  Croydon Publishing.
 
Contains:

  • Untitled story about Captain Wizard (generic red-suited hero whose only distinguishing feature is a Clark Gable mustache).
  • Race Wilkins - Marooned at the center of the earth with every fantasy creature, "the only mortal in Hades"
  • Laffs - gag strip.
  • Little Joe Djerk - Swashbuckling dramedy in the 15th Century.
  • It's True - illustrated nature facts.
  • Short Story - The Stubborn Water Ghost by Clem Colbert
  • Impossible Mann - Hugh Mann, the Impossible Man, a normal 1940s human marooned on a world of superhumans, uses his Earth knowledge of electricity to defeat the mysterious bank robber Electro.
  • Humor - gag strip.
  • The Kid Next Door - gag strip featuring silent kid who looks much like the more famous syndicated character, Henry, but with hair.
  • The Spook - gag strip.
  • The Kid Next Door
  • It's True
name: None

description: When Alan Scott gets on his usual trolley to work, he has no idea what kind of mayhem is about to be unleashed!
name: Green Lantern and the Riddle of the Runaway Trolley

description: While exploring a deserted house, Alan and Doiby discover a mail pouch filled with undelivered letters. Dating to 1857. Alan resolves to deliver the letters ... with varous to the 86-years of delay.
name: The Mail Goes Through

description:
Donna Daye, spoiled daughter of Alan Scott's boss, stages her own kidnapping as a prank. Unfortunately, her partners are actual criminals.
 
The Red Tornado story has an unusual storyline. Sheldon Mayer attempt to commit suicide following negative reactions to his stories. Tornade appears to rescue him.
name: All-American Comics

description: Seen at the seen of a crime, Green Lantern becomes the main suspect for it. With the local media painting him in the worst light possible.
name: All-American Comics
Green Lantern in "The Mystery of Marvelous Mervyn"
Green Lantern and the Mystery of the Melancholy Men
Green Lantern and the Reforming of Elegant Esmond
